	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Sep 20th 10:44 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=14376><span id=Scholar>GaelStormracer the Puissant</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>404 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.35]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Absor recently checked with the Developers and confirmed there's a semi-bug with Rain spells -- if the Rain would cause the Mob to die, it instead RESISTS IT FULLY. (Apparently this was to prevent a problem with different code that would cause the Damage from Rain spells to count as "un-owned" damage, which meant that the mobs Poofed if they died from the Rain damage).<br><br> This means that this really isn't any good to finish off a whole crowd at once; you have to chase the survivors whacking them.</p>&nbsp;<br><i><a href=HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=615518 target=akztarg>Gaell Stormracer, Epic Storm Warden of Tunare - United Kingdoms - Antonius Bayle</a></i></td></tr>
