	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f99909767617260>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=544&mid=99909767617260>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=544&mid=99909767617260>This weapon rocks</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=544&mid=99909767617260#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Aug 29th 11:07 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=91077><span id= >Zetareticuli</span></a><br><span id=notbold>6 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.33]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;  Okay I've seen too many fools putting down my weapon to stand by idly without commenting.  I will explain the pros and cons of the weapon here.  I've been using it from 28 to 36 now and this is what I've learned.<br><br>    In the open it is an awesome weapon.  Becuase of pvp restrictions the weapon will only do 66% damage to you making each rain do 47dmg.  As soon as it procs once, just step on back a bit and the rest of the rains will hit the mob.  I've had tons of procs that have done full damage to the mob and only 47dmg to me that is a huge boon.  47dmg to you and 225dmg to the enemy? I'll take that trade any day of the week.  It is also great when you get those adds.  I've partnered with clerics a few times and if you can just hold out a few more seconds, the procs will get the add down to half life by the time you kill the main one.<br><br>    Those were the pros, here are the cons.  Don't use this weapon in a dungeon.  Many dungeons have mobs that won't attack unless you attack first (either because you are a higher level than them of you have good faction with them i.e. frogloks in guk)  One rain of this weapon will often generate several adds.  Additionally, in the confined spaces of the dungeon it is hard to step back to avoid the rains.  Second con, don't use it in a group that is chain pulling because the proc will break the mez of the adds.<br><br>    There is nothing better than fighting a giant and seeing your weapon proc 2 or 3 times in a row in one fight and having the screen spam with "%t's skin blisters and burns" "%t takes 75 points of damage" over and over.  It is a thing to behold :)</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
