	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=13763><span id= >DanielSantos</span></a><br><span id=notbold>156 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.20]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>When playing my druid, I often snare and then run and wait an exact amount of time and then cast a rain spell. If timed correctly, the rain spell hits the mob at a point when he's out of my range. Then he reaches my melee range but is still in the AE range, while I am not (he's only 25 so can take hits still). This is slightly more manna effecient than my DDs.<br><br>I can't see why (especially if you are soloing), you can't back up after the 1st wave hits instead of sitting there taking a lightning bath with your buddy. Even in a group you can back out between each wave and run back in for a few seconds when you see the "target takes non-melee" message. That takes a little timing, but you have 6 seconds between waves and I will wager that it's worth it to avoid the AE even though you miss out on delivering a few hits. This can cause problems if the mob's not well taunted on the tank however (and the mob follows you), but that shouldn't happen very often. Even if it does you just stay where you are and if you didnt' move too far, the mob should still be getting hit by the last two waves while you should not.</p>&nbsp;<br>Sage Yuktii LifeStealer - 65 Necromancer 26AAs<br>Milean Treehugger - 52 Druid<br>Daaniel SilentWhisper - 51 Rogue<br>Floppee Flippee - 47 Cleric<br>Gazuk - 45 SK<br>Quellious Server</td></tr>
